# OIF — Source Code

This branch contains the source code for the OIF (Output It Forward) Chrome extension (Manifest V3).

## File structure

| File | Role |
|---|---|
| `manifest.json` | Extension configuration (Manifest V3) |
| `content.js` | Injected into HTML pages; contains the phrase list, repository domain pattern, and all detection logic |
| `background.js` | Service worker; proxies PDF fetches to handle cross-origin requests |
| `popup.html` / `popup.js` | Extension popup UI; displays results, manages storage, and exports CSV |
| `viewer.html` / `viewer.js` | Built-in PDF viewer with OIF results sidebar |
| `pdf.min.js` / `pdf_worker_min.js` | PDF.js library used to render and extract text from PDFs |
| `icon.png` | Extension icon |

## Key locations for contributors

- **Phrase list:** `phrases` array in `content.js`
- **Repository domain pattern:** `REPO_PATTERN` regex in `content.js`

Both are plain text and can be edited without programming expertise.

## Loading the extension locally

1. Go to `chrome://extensions/` and enable **Developer mode**.
2. Click **Load unpacked** and select this folder.
3. After any edits, click the reload icon next to OIF in `chrome://extensions/`.

For full usage documentation, see the [main branch README](../README.md).
